document_data.name: Easting Lane
document_data.mainbody: '''Easting Lane''' was a street in the built-up part of [[Hultail]] in [[Cormyr]].
document_data.Geography: Easting Lane was a street that stretched from southwest to northeast along the southeastern edge of built-up Hultail. In the 15{{th}} century [[DR]], the street was where [[Harrafe Orlimbur]]'s red-roofed barn with the spire stood across the street from the home and workshop of an aging seamstress named [[Avarelle Myntdown]].
